comments: Harrell (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Beverley (LAC) makes marginal contact to White's (SAS) body at the start of the drive, but the contact does not take him off his intended path to the basket.
Harrell (LAC) maintains verticality as he absorbs the contact from White (SAS) during his driving shot attempt.
Aldridge (SAS) places a resting hand on Leonard's (LAC) back that he does not extend or apply force with on his shot at the basket.
Leonard (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by DeRozan (SAS) and cleanly ties the ball up.  A jump ball is correctly called.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Shamet's (LAC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
The Replay Center confirms, the 24 second shot clock expires before White (SAS) releases the ball on his shot attempt.
Beverley (LAC) quickly grasps and releases White's (SAS) jersey without affecting his ability to maintain position during the pick.

DeRozan (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Leonard (LAC) following the pick and the contact is incidental as Leonard loses control of his dribble.  The ball, inadvertently, goes off DeRozan's foot out of bounds.
George (LAC) and Walker IV (LAC) engage and separate off-ball during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Leonard (LAC) makes marginal contact to White's (SAS) body as he gains possession of the rebound, but the contact does not affect his ability to land while maintaining his pivot foot.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Leonard's (LAC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harrell (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Walker IV's (SAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harkless (LAC) briefly places a resting hand on Aldridge's (SAS) back during the inbound, but slides it off without affecting his FOM.
Leonard (LAC) has a resting hand to DeRozan's (SAS) hip that he removes as DeRozan releases toward the ball.
Leonard (LAC) commits a take foul on DeRozan (SAS).
Shamet (LAC) and Mills (SAS) engage and separate off-ball during the inbound.
During the screen, Beverley (LAC) and Forbes (SAS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Mills (SAS) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
White (SAS) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
Mills (SAS) briefly grasps Williams' (LAC) arm during the inbound, but the contact is marginal as he immediately disengages.
Mills (SAS) commits a take foul on Williams (LAC). Williams' back is to the basket when the take foul occurs.
Beverley (LAC) legally contests White's (SAS) shot at the buzzer and incidental contact occurs as a result of White's momentum carrying him toward Beverley.
